OL,3,CUpgrading deadly road would breach
OL,4,Cgoal of cutting emissions court told
OL,6,FNo reasonable authority could have
OL,7,Fconcluded there was enough information
OL,8,Fto demonstrate the targets would still
OL,9,Fbe met if the scheme was approved,
OL,10,Faccording to the Alliance's case.
OL,12,FMr Willers contended: "We challenge
OL,13,Fthe decision taken by the Department
OL,14,Fon the basis that it amounts to a
OL,15,Fbreach of Section 52(1) of the Climate
OL,16,FChange Act 2022, and on the basis that
OL,17,Fit was irrational."
